<P CLASS="western" STYLE="margin-bottom: 0cm"><I>adjective</I></P>
<P CLASS="western" STYLE="margin-bottom: 0.5cm">adjective: <B>pragmatic</B></P>
<OL>
	<LI><P CLASS="western" STYLE="margin-bottom: 0cm">dealing with
	things <A HREF="https://www.google.com/search?client=firefox-b-d&amp;sca_esv=80d0c53c31f1ba3c&amp;sxsrf=ADLYWILAw4qzdRXhR6LqsDTmaMaa_Qs44g:1725896056586&amp;q=sensibly&amp;si=ACC90nwZKElgOcNXBU934ENhMNgq9M8JH47rH1vzMN4D6bZLEnpSGpJTsRJyXO5keDOcAAVo5Wq_GLxbtIhWtlAKFtKov02Vk7N6JN-KwAZ3bFwxfkrbolE%3D&amp;expnd=1&amp;sa=X&amp;ved=2ahUKEwi14Pzql7aIAxUlAfsDHR8qD9sQyecJegQIHBAO">sensibly</A>
	and <A HREF="https://www.google.com/search?client=firefox-b-d&amp;sca_esv=80d0c53c31f1ba3c&amp;sxsrf=ADLYWILAw4qzdRXhR6LqsDTmaMaa_Qs44g:1725896056586&amp;q=realistically&amp;si=ACC90nyj24cUGopiOVnGD91130XTnNSBqNoX1hiedUNxOHXd9EX8vJ9czQdg2hpW0lHnX75udTN4z2hO0B0IBMZ9rGQ0XVgAgAs5lk9Mn4fsrG1oldWrZ9c%3D&amp;expnd=1&amp;sa=X&amp;ved=2ahUKEwi14Pzql7aIAxUlAfsDHR8qD9sQyecJegQIHBAP">realistically</A>
	in a way that is based on practical rather than theoretical
	considerations.</P>
	<P CLASS="western">&quot;a pragmatic approach to business ethics&quot;</P>
</OL>
<P CLASS="western"><FONT SIZE=5 STYLE="font-size: 20pt">Some would
argue that the only philosophy is pragmatism. But from whence do they
obtain this &ldquo;ruling&rdquo;? Common sense? </FONT>
</P>
